cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically body perception and action in a simulated and real Nao robot. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which suggests it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of active inference and variational inference also suggests it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of a robot suggests it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics).
